{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "Because of American pressure on companies to enforce export controls, some Apple employees have refused to sell to customers of Iranian descent.", "abstract": "Op-Ed article by Jamal Abdi, policy director at the National Iranian American Council, analyzes several reports of Apple employees refusing to sell to customers of Iranian decent; holds that the incidents are the result of flawed export controls against countries like Iran that are under sanctions; argues that when retail employees are left to interpret and implement such policies, racial profiling can result.", "section_name": "Opinion", "print_page": "23", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"firstname": "Jamal", "role": "reported", "lastname": "ABDI", "rank": 1, "organization": ""}], "original": "By JAMAL ABDI", "contributor": ""}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2012/07/12/opinion/why-is-apple-discriminating-against-iranian-americans.html", "lead_paragraph": "Because of American pressure on companies to enforce export controls, some Apple employees have refused to sell to customers of Iranian descent.", "headline": {"seo": "Why Is Apple Discriminating Against Iranian-Americans?", "main": "Sanctions at the Genius Bar", "print_headline": "Sanctions at the Genius Bar", "content_kicker": "Op-Ed Contributor", "kicker": "Op-Ed Contributor"}, "_id": "53f8b83638f0d835538dce8f", "word_count": "872", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2012/07/12/opinion/0712OPEDmcquade/0712OPEDmcquade-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2012/07/12/opinion/0712OPEDmcquade/0712OPEDmcquade-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 410, "url": "images/2012/07/12/opinion/0712OPEDmcquade/0712OPEDmcquade-articleLarge-v2.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2012/07/12/opinion/0712OPEDmcquade/0712OPEDmcquade-articleLarge-v2.jpg", "xlargewidth": "600", "xlargeheight": "410"}, "subtype": "xlar